In-app purchases
Starting from version 2.3.2, we have added an in-app purchase option that allows you to remove ads and enjoy an ad-free experience.
The privacy policy regarding in-app purchases has been applied from that version onward.
Following section explains how we collect, use, and protect your personal information when you make in-app purchases:
Information Collection and Use
When you make an in-app purchase, the payment process is handled by Google Play. We do Not collect or store any personal or payment information.
All transactions and payment details are processed securely through Google Play’s Billing Library.
Data We Collect
The following information may be collected when you make an in-app purchase:
Transaction Details: Including purchase type, item, and the state of the transaction.
Device Information: Such as device model, operating system version, and unique device identifiers.
Third-Party Services
This app uses Google Play for processing in-app purchases.
Google Play's privacy practices are governed by Google’s Privacy Policy, which you can review
here
.
Data Storage
We do Not store any personal data on our servers. However, transaction-related data may be stored locally on your device for the purpose of managing your purchases within the app.
Security
We use Google Play’s secure payment system to handle all in-app purchase transactions.
We do not store any payment information directly.
Google Play ensures that all transactions are encrypted and securely processed.
GDPR and CCPA Compliance
If you are a resident of the European Union or California, you have certain rights regarding your personal data.
Since we do not collect personal data beyond what is required for in-app purchases, there is no data retention or sale by our app.
All sensitive information, such as payment details, is handled by Google Play, and you may refer to Google’s Privacy Policy for more information on how they process data.
Our app does not collect personal data directly; however, we use third-party libraries that may collect data in accordance with their own privacy policies.
For any third-party services integrated within the app, you are encouraged to review their privacy policies to understand how they may collect and process data.
The privacy policies of third-party service providers used by this app are linked in the first section of this policy.
Log Data
I want to inform you that whenever you use app, in a case of an error in the app I collect data and information (through third party products) on your phone called Log Data. This Log Data may include information such as your device Internet Protocol (“IP”) address, device name, operating system version, the time and date of your use of the app, and other statistics.
Changes to This Privacy Policy
I may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Thus, you are advised to review this page periodically for any changes (
you can access this page from the About us section in app settings
). I will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page. These changes are effective immediately after they are posted on this page.
Contact Me
If you have any questions or suggestions about my Privacy Policy, do not hesitate to contact me at
tact.techno@gmail.com
.
